spanGrp.span: ‘When we come to Buenos Aires, you coming from Germany,
Jee sa beteũ Buenos_Aires ra bas beteũ Alemania wa
You come and look for a place called Zona Sur, near Buenos Aires, Puntarenas.
Bas beteũ bas të kã' yule kã' (_) kã' kie Sona Sur Buenos_Aires wa Puntarenas
There you ask those we call alligators,
Jeska ĩã/ bas të ñẽ tlõkwa wã/ sa të kie-gẽ-ra
that is the police, you ask them for the address
polisia-wa ĩã bas të (_) í ñẽ ñala direksion chage
There Ujarraz is located directly upwards from Buenos Aires;
Jeska ra Ujarras ra je ñala Bueno(r) Buenos_Aires ska ñawösiga juigweta
you come toward the Talamanca mountain range, our home.
Sa kã' (eh) kordillera Talamanka (_) bas bötö jeska
From Buenos Aires you take the road near the school,
Buenos_Aires wa bas bötö yabla yur-gẽ kenẽga wa
Je wa bas bötö-gẽ bas tebeli_yaga inga ra
take the road from Salitre to Ujarraz.
bas të í guge ñala damãu Salitre wa ñala mãu- mĩ ji Ujarras wa
There it is written on cement how far it is to Ujarraz.
Jeska í tẽl kit-lë yayiga jãrga Ujarras bikö í kẽi she- nã ĩã ra
Jee juyukwo tsõ ke-lë jemẽ jiebi
You come through the savannah, long ago it was a savannah,
Jeska bas bötö sök kã' ĩãjiñãra sök
but now people turned it into a pinapple plantation;
jera jiwa ra pe të í kbácha rö je rö piña ebö wa
you go by the side, or in the middle.
Jewa bas bötö í kö kagrei wa í kö shawa bas bötö
There is an intersection called Olan,
and you take the Ujarraz road.
You go headwards to the riverside;
tsabataga bas dö Bikës kö wa
after the Ceibo River you go by the savannah upwards;
Bikës ska bas bötö juigweta kã' kẽi ebö Je ska bas bötö juigweta
by the road there are some white people’s houses.
There is what in the white man’s language you call puente;
jũköwa ñala wa jeska shkö-glö sikwa ktö wa kie puente blali
once you cross over you are already in the place called Ujarraz;
jeska bas köjöũ-ra je ra bas tsõ-ka se je kẽi jãrga kã' kie Ujarras
there is the school in the middle,
Jera jeska eskuela jatanã'-wã í sha ska
the church is on the left-hand side,
iglesia jatanã'-wã í sha wa í jula shulë wa
where kids are taught to await God.
You can go wherever you want.
Jeska mãĩ bas shka-gle jeska bas mĩ bas të í chage
